what is CSS?

CSS is an acronym for cascading style sheets
is used in conjunction with HTML, allows to customize
the elements and layout (design) of a webpage.

How to include?

There are three ways...

In-Line - Used for customize some few elements in the definition of itself
Internal - We create a pair of styled elements in the head of our html document, usefl for single page websites.
External - This is recognized as the best, it's about from link a css file to our html file to style 1 or all pages on a website. Useful when you make a website with a lot of pages.

Rules for declaring css properties

Ex: h1{color:green;}

1. Element
2. Property
3. Value